g.text: Incorrect code results in incorrect science
Code is science. Historically, science has been reviewed by its peers to validate it before being published.
In modern times, computer code forms part of scientific analysis, but it is rarely shared or reviewed.
This manifesto is for anyone who deals with code in a scientific setting, including publishers, researchers,
